# Publish-Copy Rule

When copying plugin artifacts to the publish repository, follow this rule.

## Inclusion (COPY ONLY these paths)

Copy these paths from toolkit repo root to publish destination. Overwrite existing files.

| Path | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `.cursor-plugin/` | Cursor manifest and plugin metadata |
| `.claude-plugin/` | Claude/Agent Plugins manifest |
| `.mcp.json` | MCP server definitions (Chrome DevTools) |
| `skills/` | Skills (wake-storefront-api, wake-checkout-flow, wake-product-variants, wake-storefront-reference-patterns, wake-hotsite-banners, web-performance-audit, and spec-derived only) |
| `agents/` | Agents (wake-storefront-developer, wake-checkout-architect, wake-migration-specialist, security-auditor, qa-expert, performance-engineer, graphql-architect, code-reviewer, and spec-derived only) |
| `rules/` | Rules (publish-copy.mdc and spec-derived only) |
| `commands/` | Commands (publish-copy, wake-product-page, wake-search-page, wake-checkout-flow, wake-migrate-storefront-query, wake-security-audit, wake-test-plan, wake-performance-review, wake-query-review, wake-code-review, and spec-derived only) |
| `README.md` | Plugin README |
| `assets/` | Logo and other marketplace assets |
| `scripts/` | Plugin utility scripts (wake-graphql-validate, wake-query-from-reference, wake-checkout-flow-validator) |

## Exclusion (NEVER copy)

Do NOT copy any of the following:

- `.bmad-core/` — Internal BMad tooling
- `.codex/` — Internal Codex tooling
- `.specify/` — Speckit workflow and memory
- `specs/` — Feature specs (toolkit-only)
- `.publish-config.json` — Local config (may contain absolute paths)
- Any agents, skills, tools, or workflows NOT created via specs
- `node_modules/`, `dist/`, `build/`, `.git/`, `*.log`, `.env*`

## Behavior

- **Overwrite**: Replace existing files at destination with toolkit copies
- **Create destination**: If destination path does not exist, create it
- **Report empty**: If no spec-derived artifacts exist to copy, report and exit
